Python PIP (package installer)

pip installs packages from PyPI (https://pypi.org/).

Common commands (run in terminal, with venv activated when possible):
  python -m pip --version
  python -m pip install package_name
  python -m pip uninstall package_name
  python -m pip list

Prefer `python -m pip` so pip matches the same Python you run.

See also: https://www.w3schools.com/python/python_pip.asp
